==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[Down's syndrome|Down’s syndrome]]

===Etymology===
Named after [[w:John Langdon-Down|John L.H. Langdon-Down]] (1828-1896), an English physician who described it in the late 1800s. The term was first used in 1961.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Down]] [[syndrome]]|-}}

# {{context|chiefly|US}} Condition caused by a [[chromosomal]] [[excess]], whereby the patients bear a certain [[resemblance]] to the [[mongoloid|Mongoloid]] race, such as a small head and [[tilt]]ed eyelids, and typically have a delay in cognitive ability and physical growth.

====Synonyms====
* [[trisomy 21]]

====Usage notes====
Known only as {{term|Down's syndrome}} in the UK.

